2.title: Chapter 17: Harder, Better, Faster, Stronger
2.plot: Mark Andrews requested that he and Eddie Dennis have their match as announced, later in the show. Dennis agreed. Rampage Brown defeated Mark Haskins by Disqualification after Mark Haskins hit Rampage Brown with a steel chair. Marty Scurll defeated El Ligero by Submission. Dave Mastiff defeated Tommy End by Pinfall. Following the match, Tommy End said that next time he returns to PROGRESS Wrestling, he won't be coming alone. Noam Dar defeated Paul Robinson by Submission. Eddie Dennis defeated Mark Andrews by Pinfall.

3.title: Sweet Jesus vs. The Faceless,
3.plot: It was announced at Chapter 9 that beginning in November 2013 there would begin a series of matches to determine the first Progress Tag Team champions. The champions were crowned at Chapter 12, the second anniversary show, in March 2014. As with the Progress Championship not being a conventional championship belt, the Progress Tag Team Championship was originally represented by a shield with the Progress eagle on the front. The shield splits into two, one for each championship holder. At Chapter 46 the Tag Team shields were replaced with traditional strap title belts,...

5.title: Chapter 19: Super Strong Style 16
5.plot: Progress have just announced the 19th Chapter in their indie promotion story: Super Strong Style 16 - Tournament Edition 2015; a two day event taking place on Sunday the 24th of May and Monday the 25th of May. That's a bank holiday, by the way, just in case the timing of the event confused you. The titular tournament will feature a plethora of top British and international talent, but don't worry if your favourite gets knocked out on the first day. 4.title: Freedom's Road 1
4.plot: The show opens with Darren Allen getting a haircut backstage. His protege's and tag partner, Earl Black Jr, is angry that Darren is cursing on trivial things like hair cuts, and not putting the effort into preparing for their upcoming match; especially as they haven't won a match as a team in months. Chakara is in the back and Pollyanna comes in and - reminiscent of Brian Kendrick begging TJ Perkins to lose - essentially begs Chakara to let her win the match. imdb.plot outline: Progress Wrestling (stylised as PROGRESS) is a British professional wrestling promotion that was established in 2011 by comedian Jim Smallman and events and comedy promoter Jon Briley, later to be joined in management of the company by actor Glen Robinson (professionally known as Glen Joseph).
